 to make a life worth living.Kaag tells how James's experiences as one of what he called the "sick-souled," those who think that life might be meaningless, drove him to articulate an ideal of "healthy-mindedness"-an attitude toward life that is open, active, and hopeful, but also realistic about its risks. In fact, all of James's pragmatism, resting on the idea that truth should be judged by its practical consequences for our lives, is a response to, and possible antidote for, crises of meaning that threaten to undo many of us at one time or another. Along the way, Kaag also movingly describes how his own life has been endlessly enriched by James.Eloquent, inspiring, and filled with insight, Sick Souls, Healthy Minds may be the smartest and most important self-help book you'll ever read.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPragmatism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Pragmatism.2bisacsh  aHarvard.  aHenry James.  aIn the Maelstrom of Modernism.  aLouis Menand.  aMetaphysical Club.  aRobert Richardson.  aSteven Rose.  aVarieties of Religious Experience.  aWilliam James "es.  aWilliam James books.  aempirical psychology.  afree will.  afreedom.  ahope.  ahow to live.  ainspirational books.  ameaning of pragmatism.  ameaninglessness.  amemoir.  anihilism.  aovercoming despair.  aovercoming determinism.  apractical philosophy.  atranscendence.  auses of pragmatism.  awhat does pragmatism mean.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110